decompress.translation[0].definitions[0]: to reduce the pressure of air on something
decompress.translation[0].definitions[1]: to change the information in a computer document back into a form that can be easily read or used, when the information was stored on the computer in a special form that used less space in the computer’s memory
Most Macintosh computers can decompress files automatically.
